{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"36":{"eng-name":"Tribulations","ara-name":"كتاب الفتن"}},"section_detail":{"36":{"hadithnumber_first":3927,"hadithnumber_last":4099,"arabicnumber_first":3927,"arabicnumber_last":4099}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3937,"arabicnumber":3937,"text":"حَدَّثَنَا حُمَيْدُ بْنُ مَسْعَدَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ زُرَيْعٍ، حَدَّثَنَا حُمَيْدٌ، حَدَّثَنَا الْحَسَنُ، عَنْ عِمْرَانَ بْنِ الْحُصَيْنِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ \"‏ مَنِ انْتَهَبَ نُهْبَةً فَلَيْسَ مِنَّا ‏\"‏ ‏.‏","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih Lighairihi"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":36,"hadith":12},"chapter":{"id":3,"ara-name":"باب النَّهْىِ عَنِ النُّهْبَةِ","eng-name":"The prohibition of plunder","isFirstHadith":false}}]}